        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 12 at 5:34PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 534 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Jacksonville to near Nacogdoches to near
Diboll. Movement was northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lufkin, Nacogdoches, Jacksonville, Henderson, Rusk, Diboll, Hudson,
Overton, Huntington, Troup, New London, Arp, Garrison, Melrose,
Ponta, New Salem, Trawick, Woden, Joinerville, and Sacul.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

These storms may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
